# Role List View Flow:

01. Header.jsp me Role List ka link banaya gaya:
    <a href="<%=ORSView.ROLE_LIST_CTL%>">Role List</a>

02. User ne Role List link par click kiya.

03. Request RoleListCtl par gayi aur doGet() method call hui.

04. doGet() method me default values set ki gayi:
    - pageNo = 1
    - pageSize = PropertyReader se liya gaya

05. populateBean(request) call hua aur RoleBean me search parameters (name, roleId) set hue.

06. RoleModel ka object banaya gaya:
    RoleModel model = new RoleModel();

07. model.search(bean, pageNo, pageSize) call hua:
    - database se role list fetch hui

08. next page check karne ke liye:
    model.search(bean, pageNo + 1, pageSize) call hua

09. Agar list null ya empty hai to:
    ServletUtility.setErrorMessage("No record found", request) set kiya gaya

10. Retrieved data ko request me set kiya gaya:
    - ServletUtility.setList(list, request)
    - ServletUtility.setPageNo(pageNo, request)
    - ServletUtility.setPageSize(pageSize, request)
    - ServletUtility.setBean(bean, request)
    - request.setAttribute("nextListSize", next.size())

11. ServletUtility.forward(getView(), request, response) call hua.

12. Request RoleListView.jsp par forward hui.

13. JSP par:
    - ServletUtility.getList(request) se list get ki gayi
    - Iterator se list loop ki gayi:
        Iterator<RoleBean> it = list.iterator();

14. while loop me har RoleBean ka data print kiya gaya:
    - name → bean.getName()
    - description → bean.getDescription()

15. Table me har record ek row ke form me display hua.

16. S.No calculate hua:
    index = ((pageNo - 1) * pageSize) + 1

17. Final output:
    Role list table format me user ko display ho gayi.
